    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-10T16:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-10T16:29:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2266½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-11T02:00:00+04:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1918, 2 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Copied from confirmation, original not
                            received.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>329. Referring to my telegram No. 328<note n="1" xml:id="d602fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_618">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            618</ref>.</note> similar telegrams also received by French and Italian
                    colleagues, tone of French telegram however stronger than others. After
                    conferring with Allied chiefs here to-night we have unanimously agreed not to
                    comply with demand. British Embassy has so advised <persName corresp="#p_PMGFC1"
                        >General Poole</persName>, Murman, <pb facs="0587" n="497" xml:id="pg_497"/>
                    and Admiral <persName>Kemp</persName>, Archangel, at the same time urging
                    immediate sending Allied troops Archangel. I am so informing Consuls, Moscow and
                    Archangel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
